<br>
they shouldnt. <br>
<br>
besides, all the epic pet does is:<br>
a) cause imbalance at lower levels (my pet at 55 does 3xs as much damage as a comparable warrior, fun fun!)<br>
b) help foster magician &quot;class gaps&quot; (those with epic and those without)<br>
c) skew perceptions of what a magician is capable of (you can only do that camp with epic, ect)..<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>all mages</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> should have a pet which is roughly the same as other mages of the same rank. mages who are &quot;uber&quot; and spend more time raiding should have pets who are a little better than other equal rank mages (through focus items).<br>
a level 53 mage who got lucky on his 7th poh trip, and knows someone with a crown from air should <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> have the best pet in the game, im sorry if you dont like the sound of that, but its fair.<br>
